7 An Act relating to the Department of Human Services;
making appropriations; stating purposes; providing an
8 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
13 Human Services, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
14 Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State Treasury, the sum of
15 Three Million Dollars ($3,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be
16 necessary to provide funding to the Boys and Girls Clubs in
17 Oklahoma. Such funds shall be utilized in a manner consistent with
18 the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic
19 Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
20 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
21 Human Services, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
22 Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State Treasury, the sum of Six
23 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($600,000.00) or so much thereof as may be
24 necessary to provide funding to the Young Women’s Christian
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1142 Page 1

1 Asso ciation (YWCA). Such funds shall be utilized in a manner
2 consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee
3 on Pandemic Relief Funding on April 15, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
7 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
9 Passed the Senate the 21st day of April, 2026.
